<div class="row" style="overflow:auto; height:500px; width:100%">
  <div class="box">
    <div class="icon">
      <div class="info" style="margin-left: 25px; background-color: white; border: none">



        <%= form_for(observer_entry) do |f| %>
            <br>


            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-5">
                <div class="field">
                  <%= f.label :observation_id, 'Who are you observing?'  %><br>
                  <%= f.collection_select :observation_id, observations, :id, :observee, :autofocus => "autofocus", :class => "form-control"    %>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-md-7">
                <div class="field">
                  <%= f.label :observed_at, 'When'  %><br>
                  <%= f.date_select :observed_at, :class => "form-control"    %>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <br>

            <div class="row">


                <% if observer_entry.errors.any? %>
                    <div id="error_explanation">
                      <h2><%= pluralize(observer_entry.errors.count, "error") %> prohibited this entry from being saved:</h2>

                      <ul>
                        <% observer_entry.errors.full_messages.each do |message| %>
                            <li><%= message %></li>
                        <% end %>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                <% end %>


                <br>



                <script>
                    var moods = ["","No sadness", "Occasional sadness in keeping with the circumstances", "Sad or low but brightens up without difficulty",
                        "Sad and lowness, with difficulty brightening up", "Pervasive feelings of sadness or gloominess. Mood influenced by external circumstances",
                        "Pervasive sadness originating internally and externally", "Continuous or unvarying sadness, misery or dispondency"];
                </script>
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="field">
                    <div class="slider-image">
                      <%=image_tag('mood_icon_0.png', style: 'height:80px;width80px', id:"img-feeling-val")%>
                    </div>
                    <div class="slider-group slider-content">
                      <div class="slider-header">Mood</div>
                      <div class="slider-custom">
                        <input type="range" class="faces" id="feeling-slider" name="observer_entry[feeling]" min="-1" max="6" value="-1" step="1" list="steplist"
                               onChange="myVal=this.value; javascript: document.getElementById('mood_text').innerHTML = moods[++myVal]" />
                      </div>
                      <div id="mood_text" class="slider-text"></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row" style="min-height:100px; width:90%">&nbsp;</div>

                <script>
                    var emotion = ["","No anxiety", "Mild. Only fleeting inner tension", "Occasional feelings of edginess and ill-defined discomfort",
                        "Common Feelings of tension and intermittent panic which can be mastered with some difficulty",
                        "Continuous feelings of inner tension or intermittent panic which can be mastered with some difficulty",
                        "Continual dread or anguish", "Unrelenting dread or anguish. Overwhelming panic"]
                </script>
                <div class="row">
                  <div class="field">
                    <div class="slider-image">
                      <%=image_tag('anxiety_icon_0.png', style: 'height:80px;width80px', id:"img-emotion-val")%>
                    </div>
                    <div class="slider-group slider-content">
                      <div class="slider-header">Anxiety</div>
                      <div class="slider-custom">
                        <input type="range" class="faces" id="emotion-slider" name="observer_entry[emotion]" min="-1" max="6" value="-1" step="1" list="steplist"
                               onChange="myVal=this.value; javascript: document.getElementById('emotion_text').innerHTML = emotion[++myVal]" />
                      </div>
                      <div id="emotion_text" class="slider-text"></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row" style="min-height:100px; width:90%">&nbsp;</div>


                <hr/>

                <div class="row">
                  <div class="field">
                    <div class="slider-image">
                      <%=image_tag('worklife.png', style: 'height:80px;width80px', id:"img-worklife-val")%>
                    </div>
                    <div class="slider-group slider-content">
                      <div class="slider-header">Work Life</div>
                      <div class="slider-custom">
                        <input type="range" id="work_life-slider" class="faces" name="observer_entry[work_life]" min="-1" max="10" value="-1" step="1"
                               onChange="updateSliderVal('work_life', this.value)" />
                      </div>
                      <div id="work_life-val" class="slider-text" style="text-align: center"></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row" style="min-height:100px; width:90%">&nbsp;</div>

                <div class="row">
                  <div class="field">
                    <div class="slider-image">
                      <%=image_tag('sociallife.png', style: 'height:80px;width80px', id:"img-socialinteraction-val")%>
                    </div>
                    <div class="slider-group slider-content">
                      <div class="slider-header">Social Life</div>
                      <div class="slider-custom">
                        <input type="range" id="social_interaction-slider" class="faces" name="observer_entry[social_interaction]" min="-1" max="10" value="-1" step="1"
                               onChange="updateSliderVal('social_interaction', this.value)" />
                      </div>
                      <div id="social_interaction-val" class="slider-text" style="text-align: center"></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row" style="min-height:100px; width:90%">&nbsp;</div>

                <div class="row">
                  <div class="field">
                    <div class="slider-image">
                      <%=image_tag('familylife.png', style: 'height:80px;width80px', id:"img-familylife-val")%>
                    </div>
                    <div class="slider-group slider-content">
                      <div class="slider-header">Family Life</div>
                      <div class="slider-custom">
                        <input type="range" id="family_life-slider" class="faces" name="observer_entry[family_life]" min="-1" max="10" value="-1" step="1"
                               onChange="updateSliderVal('family_life', this.value)" />
                      </div>
                      <div id="family_life-val" class="slider-text" style="text-align: center"></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>

                <div class="row" style="min-height:75px; width:90%">&nbsp;</div><hr/>



                <div class="actions" style="margin-top: 50px">
                  <%= f.submit "Save", class: "btn btn-primary", style: "background-color: #326867; border-radius: 0" %>
                </div>
        <%end%>
        </div>

      </div>


        <!-- Modal -->
      <div class="row">


        <div class="modal fade" id="moodModal" role="dialog">
          <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" >

            <!-- Modal content-->
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
                <h4 class="modal-title">Mood</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                Representing reports of depressed mood,
                regardless of whether it is reflected in appearance or not. Includes low spirits,
                despondency or the feeling of being beyond help and without hope. Rate
                according to intensity, duration and the extent to which the mood is reported
                to be influenced by events. <br><br>

                <i class="fa fa-smile-o"></i> ---> <i class="fa fa-frown-o"></i><br><br>

                0  - Occasional sadness in keeping with the circumstances<br><br>
                1<br><br>
                2  - Sad or low but brightens up without difficulty<br><br>
                3<br><br>
                4  - Pervasive feelings of sadness or gloominess. The mood is still influenced by external circumstances <br><br>
                5<br><br>
                6  - Continuous or unvarying sadness, misery or despondency<br><br>

              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modal fade" id="anxietyModal" role="dialog">
          <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" >

            <!-- Modal content-->
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
                <h4 class="modal-title">Anxiety</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                Representing feelings of ill-defined discomfort,
                edginess, inner turmoil, mental tension mounting to either panic, dread or
                anguish. Rate according to intensity, frequency, duration and the extent of
                reassurance called for.<br><br>
                0 - Placid. Only fleeting inner tension<br><br>
                1<br><br>
                2 - Occasional feelings of edginess and ill-defined discomfort<br><br>
                3<br><br>
                4 - Continuous feelings of inner tension or intermittent panic which can be mastered with some difficulty<br><br>
                5<br><br>
                6 - Unrelenting dread or anguish. Overwhelming panic <br><br>

              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modal fade" id="sleepModal" role="dialog">
          <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" >

            <!-- Modal content-->
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
                <h4 class="modal-title">Sleep</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                Representing the experience of reduced duration or
                depth of sleep compared to your normal sleep patterns when well.
                <br><br>
                0 - Sleeps as usual<br><br>
                1<br><br>
                2 - Slight difficulty dropping off to sleep or slightly reduced, light, or fitful sleep<br><br>
                3<br><br>
                4 - Sleep reduced or broken by at least 2 hours<br><br>
                5<br><br>
                6 - Less than 2 or 3 hours sleep<br><br>

              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modal fade" id="appetiteModal" role="dialog">
          <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" >

            <!-- Modal content-->
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
                <h4 class="modal-title">Appetite</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                Representing the feeling of a loss of appetite compared with when well. Rate by loss of desire for food or the need to force
                oneself to eat. <br><br>
                0 - Normal or increased appetite <br><br>
                1 <br><br>
                2 - Slightly reduced appetite <br><br>
                3 <br><br>
                4 - No appetite. Food is tasteless <br><br>
                5 <br><br>
                6 - Need persuasion to eat at all <br><br>

              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modal fade" id="concentrationModal" role="dialog">
          <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" >

            <!-- Modal content-->
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
                <h4 class="modal-title">Concentration</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                Representing difficulties in collecting your thoughts leading to incapacitating lack of concentration. <br>
                Rate according to intensity, frequency, and degree of incapacity produced. <br><br>
                0 - No difficulties in concentration <br><br>
                1 <br><br>
                2 - Occasional difficulties in collecting your thoughts <br><br>
                3 <br><br>
                4 - Difficulties in concentrating and sustaining thought which reduces ability to read or hold a conversation <br><br>
                5 <br><br>
                6 - Unable to read or converse without great difficulty <br><br>

              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modal fade" id="initiativeModal" role="dialog">
          <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" >

            <!-- Modal content-->
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
                <h4 class="modal-title">Initiative or Lassitude</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                Representing a difficulty getting started, or slowness initiating and performing everyday activities. <br><br>
                0 - Hardly any difficulty in getting started. No sluggishness <br><br>
                1 <br><br>
                2 - Difficulties in starting activities <br><br>
                3 <br><br>
                4 - Difficulties in simple routine activities which should be carried out with effort <br><br>
                5 <br><br>
                6 - Complete lassitude. Unable to do anything without help <br><br>

              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modal fade" id="energyModal" role="dialog">
          <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" >

            <!-- Modal content-->
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
                <h4 class="modal-title">Energy / Inability to Feel</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                Representing the subjective experience of reduced
                interest in the surroundings, or activities that normally give pleasure. The
                ability to react with adequate emotion to circumstances or people is reduced.
                0 - Normal interest in the surroundings and in other people <br><br>
                1 <br><br>
                2 - Reduced ability to enjoy usual interests <br><br>
                3 <br><br>
                4 - Loss of interest in the surroundings. Loss of feelings for friends and
                acquaintances <br><br>
                5 <br><br>
                6 - The experience of being emotionally paralysed, inability to feel anger, grief
                or pleasure, and a complete or even painful failure to feel for close
                relatives and friends <br><br>

              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modal fade" id="pessimismModal" role="dialog">
          <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" >

            <!-- Modal content-->
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
                <h4 class="modal-title">Pessimism</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                Representing thoughts of guilt, inferiority, self-reproach, sinfulness, remorse and ruin. <br><br>
                0 - No pessimistic thoughts <br><br>
                1 <br><br>
                2 - Fluctuating ideas of failure, self-reproach or self-depreciation <br><br>
                3 <br><br>
                4 - Persistent self-accusations, or definite but still rational ideas of guilt or sin. Increasingly pessimistic about the future <br><br>
                5 <br><br>
                6 - Delusions of ruin, remorse, or unredeemable sin. Self-accusations which are absurd and unshakeable <br><br>

              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="modal fade" id="zestModal" role="dialog">
          <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg" >
            <!-- Modal content-->
            <div class="modal-content">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal">&times;</button>
                <h4 class="modal-title">Hopelessness</h4>
              </div>
              <div class="modal-body">
                Representing the feeling that life is not worth
                living, that a natural death would be welcome, suicidal thoughts, and
                preparation for suicide. Suicidal attempts should not in themselves influence
                this rating. <br><br>
                0 - Enjoys life or takes it as it comes <br><br>
                1 <br><br>
                2 - Weary of life. Only fleeting suicidal thoughts <br><br>
                3 <br><br>
                4 - Probably better off dead. Suicidal thoughts are common, and suicide is
                considered as a possible solution, but without specific plans or intention <br><br>
                5 <br><br>
                6 - Explicit plans for suicide when there is an opportunity. Active preparations
                for suicide <br><br>

              </div>
              <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-default" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>